5:
Hmph. So it won't seal, even after all
this.
7:
The shifts are growing out of hand...
At this rate, I won't be able to handle
it on my own—
11:
No, I'm being ridiculous. The
Kaleidoscope is MINE to control! I am
its master, and it WILL bend to me...
18:
The effects of the primal beasts
have mostly faded, it seems.
21:
Looks that way. I wonder if Beatrix
and Zeta made it out okay...
24:
You saw firsthand how powerful
they are. I'm sure they are fine—
33:
Are you KIDDING me?! Why'd that
stupid hole spit me out HERE of all
places!
41:
Is that you, Alk? Perfect timing! Help
me out, will you?
46: Hang on, we'll pull you up!
50:
Phew! That was close! I really owe
you guys one!
55:
How'd you end up hanging off a
cliff? Actually... why're you in this
world in the first place?!
59:
...Don't tell me we're about to get
another visit from those primal
beasts too.
64:
We already beat the stuffing outta
those guys, so you don't need to
worry about them!
70:
Remember the hole that sucked us
all into this world?
72:
It's still open, so I've been checking it
out. Just to make sure no other
primal beasts snuck their way in.
79:
In other words... You're here on
patrol.
85:
You've been coming over on the
regular? You should've told us!
95:
Er, yeah! That's totally why I'm here!
Just a regular ol' patrol—not me
accidentally falling through the hole
or anything!
98:
Definitely jumped through on
purpose so I can survey the area!
102:
Besides, I've been meaning to see
you guys again! Never got to
properly say thanks the last time we
saw each other, what with all the
fighting going down!
106: Uh-huuuh... Sure, let's leave it at that.
110:
Still, I'm not sure it's a good idea for
you to explore the Kaleidoscope
alone.
115:
No need to worry on that front.
Embrasque is always with me, so I'm
never alone! Best partner ever!
121:
Ah, your seal weapon... I admit that
it's powerful, but...
127:
Nice, some target practice! Time to
prove you've got nothing to worry
about!
131:
Huh... I do have to admit, you're
pretty strong.
136:
Heheh, see? Me and Embrasque are
unstoppable!
146:
D-don't worry about it! This is
actually perfect!
151:
Wait, this is too much, even for you!
We should retreat—
157:
I do best when I'm in a pinch! Stay
back, or you'll get caught in the
crossfire!
165: Heheh, didn't even break a sweat!
171:
As impressive as that was, I thought
my heart was about to stop...
175:
Didn't Zeta tell you guys? I get
stronger the more I'm pushed into a
corner.
177:
That's why I'll be fine without
supervision—
183:
At this rate, I might actually have a
heart attack...
191:
B-but at least when it comes to
monsters, I can handle anything this
place throws at me!
196:
Clearly, the problem isn't the
monsters. What would you have
done if you'd actually fallen down
that hole?
204:
Why don't you let us help with your
survey and patrols?
208:
I mean, I'd definitely appreciate it...
But are you sure?
212:
Of course. If more primal beasts
ever came through, it would be a
problem for us as well.
217:
Yeah. To be honest, I'd feel a lot
better if I had you fighting by my
side if we ever ran into them again.
225:
I was actually a little bit worried
about going at this alone... But only
a little bit! I don't have my usual
comrades here to help, after all...
229:
So you'll just have to be my new
comrades instead!
232:
If you ever need any help too, just
ask! Comrades look out for each
other!
